article_title: Man Struck By Car While Crossing I-35 on Foot
article_text:
DES MOINES, Iowa – One man was injured Sunday night after being struck by a vehicle while he was attempting to cross Interstate 35 on foot.

The Des Moines Register reports the man was struck by a car at about 9 p.m. Sunday in the southbound lanes of I-35 near the northeast mixmaster.

The man was taken to Iowa Methodist Medical Center where he was treated for a head injury and a broken leg. His condition is not known.

Officials do not know why the man was crossing the interstate. The incident remains under investigation.
